# Certificate Pinning: Configure `/private/etc/SmartcardLogin.plist` to restrict which Certificate Authorities are trusted
#  - https://support.apple.com/guide/deployment/advanced-smart-card-options-dep7b2ede1e3/web
#  - https://github.com/frankmorgner/OpenSCToken
# OpenSCToken: A tool to enable OpenSC to work with macOS CryptoTokenKit.


# Local Account Pairing: Insert the card, follow the prompt to pair, which links it to your macOS user profile for login.
# Certificate Requirements: The card should have certificates in slots 9a (PIV Authentication) and 9d (Key Management) for maximum compatibility.
# Troubleshooting: If the card works in terminal but not in browsers, ensure OpenSC is correctly installed, and check if pkcs11 modules are properly recognized.
